The paper focuses on the development of autonomous robots for retail environments, which involves perception, knowledge processing, and manipulation tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a knowledge-enabled perception system, which involves combining diverse information sources, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions knowledge processing methods and manipulation skills, which suggest that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of a PR2 robot, which is a type of robot commonly used in control systems, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
